devdoc.details: Adheres to - IJBTiered721Delegate: General interface for the methods in this contract that interact with the blockchain's state according to the protocol's rules.Inherits from - JB721Delegate: A generic NFT delegate. Votes: A helper for voting balance snapshots. Ownable: Includes convenience functionality for checking a message sender's permissions before executing certain transactions.

getPastTotalSupply(uint256).details: Returns the total supply of votes available at the end of a past block (`blockNumber`). NOTE: This value is the sum of all available votes, which is not necessarily the sum of all delegated votes. Votes that have not been delegated are still part of total supply, even though they would not participate in a vote. Requirements: - `blockNumber` must have been already mined

getPastVotes(address,uint256).details: Returns the amount of votes that `account` had at the end of a past block (`blockNumber`). Requirements: - `blockNumber` must have been already mined

params._account: The account to check for a delegate of.

params._tierId: The ID of the tier to mint within.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.
